text: Kern Canyon is a canyon and stream in Stanislaus County, California. The mouth of the stream of Kern Canyon is located at an elevation of 302 feet / 92 meters just beyond the mouth of the Canyon on the west side of Interstate 5 in California. Its source is located at at an elevation of 1,725 feet / 526 meters in the Diablo Range. ==References== Category:Rivers of San Joaquin County, California Category:Rivers of Stanislaus County, California Category:Tributaries of the San Joaquin River Category:Diablo Range Category:Geography of the San Joaquin Valley Category:Rivers of Northern California
